Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Root cause of the '2D / nothing working' report:

1. ALL new 3D was gated behind isAuthed, and the landing was never upgraded
   to Babylon — so with sign-in broken (missing env vars) you only ever saw
   the old 2D landing.
2. Env vars (.env) are gitignored and never deploy to Vercel.

Fixes:

- / (landing) now renders a full-bleed Babylon 'Cosmic Gateway' scene with
  auth CTAs floating over it. Renders with ZERO env vars / no login — the
  overhaul is visible the instant a visitor arrives.
- /world is now an interactive Babylon 'Hub of Doors': PBR marble hall, 24
  columns, shadow-casting sun, 12 clickable doors that portal-dive to each
  world/section. No login to SEE it.
- Landing links to the hub ('Explore the Hub of Doors — no sign-in required').
- SETUP_LIVE.md: exact env-var list + how to disable Vercel SSO protection.

Local only — this session's GitHub connection is closed; push from a new
session.

Co-authored-by: arena-agent <297053741+arena-agent@users.noreply.github.com>
